"title": "6661: freedom, and the law",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6661: freedom, and the law",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ sets his people free from the condemnation and oppression of the law. Through the Holy Spirit, believers are able to fulfil the law obediently according to God's intentions.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ sets believers free from the law</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's life of perfect obedience to the law was the fulfilment of it</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:17\">MAT 5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:5\">GAL 4:4–4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22\">1PE 2:22</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's death fulfils the demands of the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:27\">HEB 7:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:11\">HEB 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:26-Heb9:28\">HEB 9:26–9:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:11-Heb10:14\">HEB 10:11–10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:24\">1PE 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>On account of Jesus Christ's death, believers can be righteous independently of the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:21-Rom3:26\">ROM 3:21–3:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:17\">JHN 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:4\">ROM 10:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:9\">PHP 3:9</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are set free from the law's condemnation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:21-Gal3:25\">GAL 3:21–3:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:1-Rom6:14\">ROM 6:1–6:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:1-Rom7:6\">ROM 7:1–7:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13\">GAL 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:5\">GAL 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:21-Gal4:31\">GAL 4:21–4:31</a> <em>The lives of Abraham, Sarah, Hagar, Ishmael and Isaac are interpreted figuratively, to illustrate the believer's freedom from the law's condemnation</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1\">GAL 5:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:14-Eph2:15\">EPH 2:14–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13-Col2:14\">COL 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>The freedom of believers rests on the power of the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:1-Rom7:6\">ROM 7:1–7:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:17-2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:17–3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1-Rom8:17\">ROM 8:1–8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:18\">GAL 5:16–5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:26\">GAL 5:22–5:26</a></p>\n<h2>The believer's freedom to obey the law voluntarily</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:32\">PSA 119:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:31\">PSA 37:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:45\">PSA 119:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:97\">PSA 119:97</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33\">JER 31:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:3\">2CO 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:25\">JAS 1:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:12\">JAS 2:12</a></p>",
